Process of systematically handling changes to a system in a way that it maintains integgrity over time. 

Sample configuration management tools available in market:
	- Puppet
	- Ansible
	- Chef
	- Salt

Benefits:
- Quick provisioning of new servers
- Quick Recovery from Critical Events
- No More Snowflake SErvers - Eliminates the question on which changes were made, configuration tweaks, manua hotfixes, software updates - these which turn servers into snowflakes are eliminated with properly documented automating script/ procedures necessary fro bringing up new server or updating an existing one will be all documented in provisioning scripts
- Version Control for the Server Environment - One has the ability to apply to the server environment many of the tools and workflows you normally use for software source code
- Replicated Environments
